## Infrastructure Database Replication Configuration

### Replication Group Configuration

| Setting | Value |
|---------|-------|
| Replication Group Name | `{{ infrastructure_replication_group | upper }}` |
| Source Database | `{{ platform_database_name | upper }}` |
| Source Account | `{{ snowflake_org_name | upper }}.{{ org_account_name | upper }}` |
{%- if replication_schedule == 'Manual only' %}
| Refresh Schedule | Manual (on-demand) |
{%- else %}
| Refresh Schedule | {{ replication_schedule }} |
{%- endif %}

### What's Being Replicated

The following objects from `{{ platform_database_name | upper }}.{{ governance_name | upper }}` will be replicated to all target accounts:

**Tags:**
- `DOMAIN` - Business unit identifier
- `ENVIRONMENT` - SDLC stage (dev, test, prod)
- `DATAPRODUCT` - Data product identifier
- `WORKLOAD` - Workload type
- `ZONE` - Data zone
- `DATA_CLASSIFICATION` - Data sensitivity level

**Network Rules (if created in Security & Identity task):**
- Allowed network rules (e.g., `corporate_vpn`, `cloud_services`)
- Blocked network rules (if configured)

**Views (if created in Cost Management task):**
- `cost_by_domain` - Credit usage by domain
- `cost_by_environment` - Credit usage by environment
- `untagged_warehouses` - Resources missing required tags

### Key Difference from Sharing

Unlike shared databases (which are read-only), replicated databases create **local copies** of all objects. This means:

| Capability | Shared Database | Replicated Database |
|------------|-----------------|---------------------|
| View tags | ✅ Yes | ✅ Yes |
| Apply tags to local objects | ❌ No | ✅ Yes |
| Reference network rules | ❌ No | ✅ Yes |
| Query views | ✅ Yes | ✅ Yes |
| Modify objects | ❌ No | ❌ No (read-only replica) |

### Creating Secondary Replication Groups

When you create additional accounts in your organization, you'll need to create a secondary replication group:

```sql
-- Run in the target account (as ACCOUNTADMIN)
CREATE REPLICATION GROUP {{ infrastructure_replication_group | upper }}
  AS REPLICA OF {{ snowflake_org_name | upper }}.{{ org_account_name | upper }}.{{ infrastructure_replication_group | upper }};
```

Then refresh to create the replica database:

```sql
-- Initial refresh to pull the database
ALTER REPLICATION GROUP {{ infrastructure_replication_group | upper }} REFRESH;
```

This creates a local copy of the infrastructure database that automatically stays in sync.

### Adding New Accounts

When new accounts are created, grant them access to the replication group:

```sql
-- Run in the Organization Account
ALTER REPLICATION GROUP {{ infrastructure_replication_group | upper }} 
  SET ALLOWED_ACCOUNTS = {{ snowflake_org_name | upper }}.<new_account_name>;
```